  "content": "workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-kernel filter_tests -- --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL — `post_filter_metadata` function doesn't exist\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `post_filter_metadata` function**\n\nAdd to `retriever.rs` (above the test module):\n\n```rust\n/// Post-filter search results by metadata fields (Option A from docs workflow spec).\n/// Applied after vector search, before returning to caller.\npub fn post_filter_metadata(\n    results: Vec<SearchResult>,\n    content_role: Option<&str>,\n    source_origin: Option<&str>,\n) -> Vec<SearchResult> {\n    if content_role.is_none() && source_origin.is_none() {\n        return results;\n    }\n    results.into_iter().filter(|r| {\n        if let Some(role) = content_role {\n            if r.entry.metadata.content_role.as_deref() != Some(role) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        if let Some(origin) = source_origin {\n            if r.entry.metadata.source_origin.as_deref() != Some(origin) {\n                return false;\n            }\n        }\n        true\n    }).collect()\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-kernel filter_tests -- --nocapture`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Wire post-filter into `VectorRetriever` and `GraphExpandRetriever`**\n\nIn each retriever's `retrieve` method, after the visibility/RBAC filtering and before returning, add:",
